                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At meetings of the Committee of Ministers of the Council of Europe on August 8
                    and 9, preceding the first meeting of the Council at Strasbourg on August 10,
                    Spaak proposed that among other things the Council consider its role in the
                    economic field. Bevin stated that the <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss>
                    would not last forever and that the Council should give some thought to
                    machinery for future European economic cooperation. His view was adopted with
                    the understanding that the work of existing organizations such as <gloss
                        target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> would be taken into account. (For other
                    references to the Council of Europe, see <ref target="#pg_1">pages 1</ref>
                    ff.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
